Jan 4 2007 	Nice Hotel Nicer Staff	My wife and I stayed at the Euro Hotel for three nights in October. The hotel is located inbetween two tube stops. About a ten minute walk to each. The room we were was not real spacious but was adequate. There is no lift in the hotel so for us, being on the 5th floor, it was a hike going up with luggage. But, once we got there and parked our luggage in the room, it wasn't too bad. The free breakfast in the morning was very good with eggs, bacon, sausage and juices and coffee. The staff at the Euro seem to be all younger women from Poland. They were very friendly and helped out with directions and sights. There is a computer with an internet connection in the lobby that is free to use. The hotel is near the British Museum and around the corner there is a pub for the late night drink. There is also a student housing complex around the corner that has some retail shops and a Starbucks there. Overall, we were very happy with the hotel and the staff.	
Dec 16 2006 	Clean hotel welcoming staff	Stayed 2 nights mid December 2006.Arrived late (2 in the morning) and was greeted by a very friendly woman who just gave me my key and said &quot;we'll do the paper work in the morning&quot;. Nice touch when you just want to get up and sleep (by the way: the check in woman was also very friendly).I had a single room. It was very very small but also clean. And who really needs more in London than a bed, a closet and clean surroundings.From the hallway I saw a family room (?), and it also looked nice and with plenty of space.The area is OK - actually quite British - and you are just a short walk from restaurants, deli's, tube, etc.Ole, Denmark	
Dec 11 2006 	great stay!	I stayed at the Euro Hotel in August 2006 for a few days. I wanted to stay in Bloomsbury as I was at university there and know the area. I was impressed with the hotel. Nearly every hotel I have been in in London is very economic with space. If you want an old building, rooms will be small and staircases steep. So I was not surpised that my single room just had room for the bed and the wardobe. However, the room was very clean, as was the shower and toilette that I had to share as I did not want to spend more money for the ensuite room. I was impressed how well kept shower and toilette were and had no problem using them.The staff at the hotel was very friendly. I was travelling with my sister and her husband and they took care that we had adjoining rooms. We could even use the balcony to go and visit each other! However, the balcony is tiny, I think you could not really sit out there. Breakfast was good, too!Besides that the location is great, Russel Square tube is only a bit away and there are lots of different bus lines around to take you many different places. I really love using the bus instead of the tube and sit on the top of the doubledecker busses. I was impressed how much the area has improved in the last year. The Brunswick Shopping Centre just next to the tube station has been renovated and there were a number of shops supposed to open this autumn.	
Sep 22 2006 	Good little hotle for a budget traveler	In planning my weekend to London I read through many hotel reviews, most of which expressed negative reviews about their lodging experiences so I had very low expectations. I chose the Euro Hotel for its price and the pictures on the web made it seem charming. A friend and I stayed for two nights and found the place very decent and the hosts quite pleasant and helpful. Beware, however, there is NO lift so if you stay there, pack lightly. We stayed on the top floor in a room with a double and single bed. The room had a sink, wardrobe, TV and they left us plenty of towels. Two bathrooms and showers were down the hall and although the hotel was booked, we never passed another soul in the hallway. The showers were clean, if small and had low water pressure. The bathrooms were also surprisingly clean. I found the breakfast to be very good. They offered a variety of cereals, coffee, fresh juices and/or a standard english breakfast comprised of sausage, bacon, egg, tomato and baked beans. The dining hall was pleasant, a very nice place to relax and plan your day in London. There was a computer in the corner for guests to use. They also happily held our luggage the day of check out until we returned for them. Overall, a very good experience!	
Jul 13 2006	A Pleasant Find	My family (2 Adults/2 Children) just stayed at the Euro Hotel for one night on July 11th. We stayed in the ensuite quad for 109 pounds, incl tax and breakfast. We had a very pleasant experience and would definitely stay at the Euro Hotel again.The room was an excellent price for location, convenience, comfort and amenities. The Russel Sq underground is about 4 short blocks away and the Euston station underground is about 6 blocks (connection to paddiington station and heathrow express). Though the hotel is set off the main drag onto gardened street, on the main streets there are plenty of restaurants and pubs within a block or two. There are even a vegetarian restaurant and a laundrette within three blocks.Our beds and room were lovely. Everything was neat and clean and the carpets and walls and paint in great condition. The halls were carpeted, so the hotel stayed pretty quiet. Our room was large and overlooked the garden/park. We had three large windows and high ceillings. Our beds (1 double, 2 twins) were comfortable and we had no trouble sleeping. It was a sunny, bright and cheery room. The shower and bathroom were smallish, but there were plenty of towels and shampoo and soap. I should warn you that there is no lift, so pack light if you plan to stay here (if fact, you should pack light anyway -- your back will thank you!).The breakfast was terrific. They offered a complete english breakfast (eggs, bacon, sausage, beans, tomato, toast, cereal, juice, coffee) in their rate. In the lobby/breakfast room is a computer which guests can use.Amenities in the room included a TV, phone, fan, coffee/tea makings, desk, and they provided a blow dryer when I asked for one.I would highly recommend the Euro Hotel and I am sure I/we will stay with them again next time we are in London.	
Apr 28 2006	Better than expected budget deal	I got an excellent deal on a single for a one night stopover, and was not disappointed at all by the Euro. The room was unremarkable but large for London, especially at this price, and the bathroom was modern and clean. My only niggle was that it was extremely hot, though not unbearable with the window open and the groovy 70s ceiling fan turned on!The location is a real plus, on a very quiet Bloomsbury street overlooking a bit of greenery, and within easy walking distance of Euston, Kings Cross and many central London attractions. The service was excellent - staff were extremely helpful, polite and friendly. Breakfast was straightforward but good, and served in a lovely sunny dining room. All in all, an above average budget option, a pleasantly characterful alternative to the Travel/Premier/Holiday Inns and Lodges.	
